monday, wednesday, friday

2. Response time to communication expectations
6 hours on weekday, 12 on weekends

3. Definition of done: when is a task complete? (hint: "I'm done with that but I didn't check it in to github" is not done.)
Code is completed, tested, and verified by at least one other person

4. Scrum meeting format/frequency and distribution of documentation tasks (meeting minutes, updating task board)
10-30 minutes: monday, wednesday, friday, possibly weekends
checkin to discord daily


5. Procedure for adopting policies (e.g. code style, code check-in steps, documentation updates) 
agree upon one format and set that before starting to code
majority vote, bring up at scrum meeting
 
6. Procedure for handling a member who is not meeting expectations
First talk to them, ask whats up, if consistently not meeting their expectations, come together as group and talk about it (re-deviding work, solutions, etc.)



